Power Deals Only Cover 33% Of Calif 2001 Needs -Official Updated: Wednesday=
,=20
March 21, 2001 06:31 PM ET Email this article to a friend!=20
Printer-friendly version=20
NEW YORK (Dow Jones)--Power contracts announced early this month by=20
California Gov. Gray Davis will only cover one-third of the electricity the=
=20
state needs to buy in 2001, according to a report by the state's chief=20
negotiator.=20
That coverage is far less than California officials originally led observer=
s=20
to believe they had secured, and the gap raises questions about whether the=
=20
state will be able to afford to keep the lights on this summer.=20

